<seg id=1> Wangma "Opens Up" Domestically By Offering Technology To The People </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> THIS NEWSPAPER'S WIRE Beijing, Jan. 5, He Huangbiao reporting: Wangma Computer Corporation, based in Beijing's Zhongguancun district, held a press conference in the Great Hall of the People on January 4 to announce their offer of a complete set of their software product, "Wangma Software", for free. This software could have earned them more than one million yuan. The reason for the offer is to satisfy the automation requirements of party, government and military departments. The whole set of software is on floppy disk, without encoding, and is "open" to the domestic market, meaning that any domestic personal computer user can copy it. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Wangma Computer Corporation became famous when its computer expert, Wang Yongmin, invented a Chinese text encoding system called "Wubi Zixing". </seg>
<seg id=4> This simple, highly effective text input method is used by more than 85 percent of China's computer users. It is the country's leading input method for Chinese. </seg>
<seg id=5> With the fast-paced development of the computer industry, more and more computer users are now lining up to buy both the new version of "Wubi Zixing" and Wangma's Chinese operating system. </seg>
<seg id=6> For the benefit of society, Wangma Computer Corporation firmly gave up on an opportunity to make huge profits, making the unencrypted floppy disk available for users so that they can copy it themselves. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Wangma Computer Corporation's selfless decision has received high praise from leaders, experts and users. </seg>
</p>
